properties.abstract: Amid the peaks of the Silvretta region between the duty-free enclave of Samnaun and Ischgl, this mountain bike tour offers lots of highlights, in addition to the marvellous mountain backdrop. Superfast single and flow trails make the downhill runs an amazing experience.
properties.description:
The mountain bike tour begins at the base station of the Ravaisch mountain lifts. Take the cable car to easily and conveniently reach Alp Trida Sattel in just a few minutes. A short traverse on the flowy Trider Sattel Trail takes you to Alp Trida where you hop on the next chairlift to Flimsattel. Make sure you take a look around when you’re on the lift. The landscape of Alp Trida is full of boulders. It was named for this view after a rockslide from Bürkelkopf. (Trida is Romansh for desolate.)

When you arrive at Flimsattel, enjoy the beautiful backdrop with mountains from the three countries that meet here: Switzerland, Austria and Italy. From Viderjoch the tour follows the border between Austria and Switzerland to Greitspitz, the highest point of the tour at 2867 m. The views from the peak across the mountains of Samnaun are spectacular.

Via Salaaser Kopf and Hüttenboden you enter the flowy Schmuggler Trail (Smugglers‘ trail). This part includes a number of technical passages. You then continue to Alp Trider Sattel. Have a bite to eat in the restaurant, before you start the downhill run via the flow trail to Alp Trida and the Duty Free Ride to Laret. The Duty Free Ride is a combination of tight and wide turns with some steep passages in rocky terrain – always accompanied by the fantastic views of the Samnaun Valley. Once you arrive in the valley, there is a last highlight to look forward to: a trail full of roots leads from Ravaisch through a quiet forest section to the village of Samnaun.
